# Environment variables for the nanoclaw-travel plugin.
#
# Production runtime: secrets are injected via OneCLI vault, not via a .env
# file. This file documents the contract for new maintainers and for local
# development.
#
# GitHub Actions secrets configuration (TESSL_TOKEN and any future
# repo-scoped secrets):
# https://github.com/jbaruch/nanoclaw-travel/settings/secrets/actions

# byAir streamable-HTTP MCP endpoint with personal API key inline.
# Get from https://byairapp.com/mcp/ — requires Pro subscription.
# Rotate in-app if exposed; rotation invalidates previous clients immediately.
BYAIR_MCP_URL=https://api.byairapp.com/mcp?api_key=REPLACE_ME

# Google Maps Distance Matrix API key for traffic-aware time-to-leave.
# Create at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials and enable
# the Distance Matrix API in the same project.
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# TomTom API key — backup routing provider, used only when the Google
# Distance Matrix call fails. Optional: absent it, the client runs
# Google-only and a Google failure propagates. Create a free key (no
# card) at https://developer.tomtom.com/ with Search + Routing enabled.
TOMTOM_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# Calendar reconciliation (#55) needs NO variable here. It calls the native
# Google Calendar REST API, and OneCLI's TLS-MITM gateway injects the OAuth
# Bearer on the wire and refreshes it (nanoclaw#638) — this container holds no
# Google credential at all. The COMPOSIO_API_KEY / COMPOSIO_USER_ID pair this
# replaced is retired; delete any leftover values from the vault. If calendar
# writes fail, the problem is the gateway or the app connection, not a missing
# variable here: `reconcile.py` reports it as {"error": "gateway"} or
# {"error": "tier"} with an actionable diagnostic on stderr.

# TripIt → Reclaim timezone sync (#748) runs the `reclaim-tripit-timezones-sync`
# CLI IN THIS CONTAINER and hard-requires the OneCLI gateway to be engaged; the
# `nightly-travel-sync` Step 1 wrapper (`scripts/sync-tripit.sh`) fails fast when
# ONECLI_URL is unset. These are NOT set in this file — the orchestrator injects
# them onto the agent spawn (jbaruch/nanoclaw `applyOneCliToSpawn`). Listed so
# the runtime contract is discoverable without reverse-engineering the script.
# The TripIt/Reclaim credentials themselves are vaulted (secret 963d7b7f, path
# injection; 12c52a66, header) — the container only ever sends placeholders the
# gateway swaps, so none of them appear here.
#
# ONECLI_URL — the gateway base, e.g. http://host.docker.internal:PORT. A URL,
#   not a secret. Gates OneCLI mode; the sync aborts if it is unset.
ONECLI_URL=http://host.docker.internal:PORT
# ENABLE_OOO — set to 1 so out-of-office blocks stay enabled under gateway mode
#   (in non-gateway mode the package inferred OOO from the now-deleted GOOGLE_*
#   vars). Injected onto the spawn alongside ONECLI_URL.
ENABLE_OOO=1
# HTTPS_PROXY / NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS — the gateway proxy and MITM CA, also spawn-
#   injected by the orchestrator; the CLI routes outbound HTTPS through them.

# CI reviewer secret(s) for the jbaruch/coding-policy gh-aw PR review
# workflows — set as GitHub Actions repository secrets (see the secrets
# link in the header above).
CODEX_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
TESSL_TOKEN=
